com.paydiant.android.ui.service.receipt

Class ReceiptRetrievalListenerAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.paydiant.android.ui.service.receipt.ReceiptRetrievalListenerAdapter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IReceiptRetrievalListener, IReceiptRetrievalWithSplitTenderInfoListener

    public class ReceiptRetrievalListenerAdapter
extends Object
implements IReceiptRetrievalWithSplitTenderInfoListener
    This class provides an empty implementation for IReceiptRetrievalListener. Any classes that wants to use only a subset of the listener methods can override the relevant methods and use it as the interface implementation. 

     ReceiptRetrievalListenerAdapter receiptRetrievalListenerAdapter = new ReceiptRetrievalListenerAdapter() {
 
    @Override
    public void onReceiptListRetrievalSuccess(ReceiptList receiptList) {
    }
 
    @Override
    public void onReceiptRetrievalError(PaydiantException e) {
    }
 };
 iReceiptRetrievalService.setReceiptRetrievalListener(receiptRetrievalListenerAdapter);
    Note: App developers are encouraged to use the ListenerAdapter implementations whenever possible as the Listener interfaces might get updated with new functionality/methods from one SDK release to the other. Therefore using a ListenerAdapter will make sure that there wont be any compilation issues due to unimplemented methods during a SDK upgrade.
